                "text_EN": "On that day,Inori was standing on the coast, as he usually did, but the ships were late. When they finally came into sight, something tore at his heart. They were eerily quiet; the wind carried no sound or call of greeting from the boat, the faces of his father and the fishermen were solemn. That day, there was no market, and no fish either. Men gathered to share a strange silence while patching up the fishnets. Inori joined Father - the net was full of enormous holes as if something had ripped it apart. Repairing the net was long and tedious work. The worst part was that Father did not speak a word. They sat silently beside the net, late into the night, and Inori could not fall asleep easily.",
